Date: 13 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong - Department of Health 13 Apr 2003 [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>

Situation report on atypical pneumonia 13 Apr 2003
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
As of 1 PM 13 Apr 2003, an additional 42 patients with symptoms of atypical
pneumonia were admitted to public hospitals. They include 9 healthcare
workers (4 from Alice Ho Miu Ling Nethersole Hospital, 2 from Princess
Margaret Hospital, 2 from Prince of Wales Hospital, and one from Queen
Elizabeth Hospital) and 5 patients from Amoy Gardens. The remaining 28 were
new patients and contacts of patients with atypical pneumonia.
A total of 223 patients have recovered from atypical pneumonia and have
been discharged from public hospitals. Of them, 8 were discharged today.
Most of the patients currently in hospital are showing positive responses
to the new treatment protocol. 122 patients are receiving treatment in
intensive care units.
5 patients died in hospitals last night and this morning, bringing to 40
the total number of deaths relating to atypical pneumonia. A 40-year-old
male died in United Christian Hospital. 2 men, aged 41 and 52, a
45-year-old female and a 66-year-old female with a history of chronic
disease died in Princess Margaret Hospital.
The cumulative figures for patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with atypical pneumonia since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows:
Cumulative number of reported cases/ total no. discharged cases/ no. deaths
(all reported cases have evidence of pneumonia)
Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students: 276/ 91/ 40
Patients, family members & visitors: 874 / 132 / 0
Total: 1150 / 223 / 40
* Most of the deaths occurred in individuals who have a history of
chronic diseases, or were patients who sought treatment at a relatively
late stage of infection.
--
